THE VISUAL THESIS:
UNJYNX = Linear's craft + Apple Watch rings + GitHub heatmap + Duolingo streaks + Headspace calm
All in midnight purple + gold. No other app looks like this. No other app COULD.
The brand colors alone make every screenshot unmistakable on any app store page.



========================================================================
PART 6: LIGHT MODE — EQUALLY DESIGNED, DISTINCTLY UNJYNX
========================================================================

CORE PHILOSOPHY: Light mode is NOT "dark mode with inverted colors." It is a
PARALLEL design system where purple becomes text, gold becomes richer, and
the app feels warm instead of clinical. Both modes must feel premium and
unmistakably UNJYNX. A user switching themes should feel like the same brand
in a different mood — midnight velvet vs morning silk.

KEY PRINCIPLE: #F8F5FF not #FFFFFF. Pure white is clinical. #F8F5FF has a
subtle purple warmth that users feel subconsciously. Todoist uses #FEFDFC.
Notion uses warm gray. Premium apps NEVER use pure white.


## 6.1 LIGHT MODE COLOR PSYCHOLOGY

Dark mode = focused, intense, "night shift energy"
Light mode = open, airy, "morning coffee energy"

In light mode, the brand presence shifts:
- Purple (#1A0533) BECOMES the text color (18.5:1 contrast — better than black!)
- Gold shifts #FFD700 -> #B8860B (Dark Goldenrod, 4.8:1 contrast — gold washes out on white otherwise)
- Emerald deepens #10B981 -> #059669
- Amber deepens #F59E0B -> #D97706
- Rose deepens #F43F5E -> #E11D48
- Channel brand colors deepen: WhatsApp #25D366->#16A34A, Telegram #06B6D4->#0891B2

The brand is ALWAYS visible. In dark mode through surface colors. In light mode through text colors.


## 6.2 LIGHT MODE GLASSMORPHISM (Different Technique)

Dark glassmorphism: translucent white on dark = frosted glass glow
Light glassmorphism: translucent white on light = soft frosted pane

LIGHT GLASS CARD:
  ClipRRect(borderRadius: 16, child: BackdropFilter(
    filter: ImageFilter.blur(sigmaX: 8, sigmaY: 8),  // less blur than dark (8 vs 12)
    child: Container(decoration: BoxDecoration(
      color: Colors.white.withOpacity(0.65),           // more opaque (0.65 vs 0.08)
      borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16),
      border: Border.all(
        color: UnjynxColors.brandViolet.withOpacity(0.08), // subtle purple border
      ),
      boxShadow: [BoxShadow(
        color: Color(0x0F1A0533),  // purple-tinted shadow, NOT gray
        blurRadius: 8, offset: Offset(0, 2),
      )],
    ))
  ))

KEY DIFFERENCES:
- Blur: 8px (not 12) — light backgrounds don't need as much diffusion
- Opacity: 65% white (not 8%) — needs more fill to be visible on light bg
- Shadow: purple-tinted rgba(26,5,51,0.06) — NEVER generic #000 shadow
- Border: visible 1px purple border rgba(107,33,168,0.08) — needed for definition
- Hero cards: purple-to-richGold gradient border (not purple-to-electricGold)

RESULT: Cards feel like frosted lavender panes floating above a warm purple mist.
This is a DISTINCTLY different aesthetic from dark mode, not just colors swapped.


## 6.3 LIGHT MODE LIVING GRADIENT BACKGROUND

Dark uses deep animated mesh. Light uses SUBTLE warm washes.

PRODUCTIVE: #F8F5FF -> #F0EAFC with faint lavender shimmer particles
IDLE: pure #F8F5FF, no animation (calm, clean)
ALL DONE: #F8F5FF -> warm #FFF8E1 (gold wash) tint + sparse gold particles (30% opacity of dark mode)
OVERDUE: #F8F5FF with very subtle warm pink tint in one corner
GHOST MODE FROM LIGHT: crossfade #F8F5FF -> deep purple gradient (400ms, seamless)

Particle counts: 30% of dark mode. Light mode is about CLARITY, dark about IMMERSION.
Movement: 5-10% of dark mode drift. Light should feel still and focused.


## 6.4 SCREEN-BY-SCREEN LIGHT MODE ENHANCEMENTS

A1. SPLASH:
- Light mode splash: white bg -> purple UNJYNX text materializes (not particles — too noisy on light)
- Logo in deep purple (#1A0533) + gold accent (#B8860B)
- Clean, editorial reveal: logo letter-by-letter with purple ink feel
- Transition to Home: logo fades into position as app bar title

A2. LOGIN:
- Background: #F8F5FF with very subtle purple radial gradient center
- Glass card: white 85% opacity + purple-tinted shadow + purple border
- Social buttons: white cards with subtle purple shadow, provider icon full color
- Tagline in midnight purple (#1A0533), gold underline uses #B8860B

B1-B4. ONBOARDING:
- Carousel backgrounds: soft gradient washes per slide (not deep gradients)
  Slide 1: #F8F5FF -> #F0EAFC (lavender wash)
  Slide 2: #F8F5FF -> #EDE5F7 (deeper lavender for channel showcase)
  Slide 3: #F8F5FF -> #FFF8E1 (warm gold wash for the "your way" feeling)
- Chain link progress: deep purple chains, gold spark on break
- Category cards (Step 4): white cards + purple shadow + purple text
  Active = gold wash bg (#FFF8E1) instead of gold glow
- Interactive elements: purple outlines, gold fills on selection

C1. HOME SCREEN (The Most Important Light Mode Screen):
- Background: solid #F8F5FF (no gradient mesh in light — clarity > immersion)
- Greeting: midnight purple (#1A0533) text. "Good morning" feels warm on light.
- Streak flame: same Rive animation but with richer orange/gold on light bg
  (fire looks MORE natural on light backgrounds — like a real flame in daylight)
- Progress Rings: ring colors UNCHANGED (Gold/Violet/Emerald are vibrant enough)
  Background track: rgba(107,33,168,0.06) instead of rgba(255,255,255,0.05)
  Center text: #1A0533. Completion glow: #B8860B shimmer.
- Daily Content Card: white card + purple-tinted shadow + subtle purple border
  Quote text (Playfair Display): #1A0533 (midnight purple — rich, editorial contrast)
  Category badge: deep violet bg + white text (same as dark — stays punchy)
  Share card light mode variant: purple bg + gold text (inverts for social sharing drama)
- Task Cards: white bg (#FFFFFF) + purple-tinted shadow
  Priority glow: P1 = rich gold (#B8860B) left edge, P2 = deep amber (#D97706)
  Overdue: deep rose (#E11D48) left border + subtle pink tint on card
  Checkbox: deep purple ring, fills with #B8860B gold on completion
  Strikethrough: purple wipe (not gold — more visible on white)
  Text: #1A0533 primary, #6B21A8 secondary, #475569 tertiary
- Quick Actions: purple-bordered glass pills on light. Active = gold wash fill (#FFF8E1)
- AI Whisper: white card, purple shadow. Crystal ball icon in deep violet.

D1. QUICK CREATE (Light):
- Sheet bg: #FFFFFF with purple-tinted shadow at top edge
- Text input: white field, purple border on focus, gold cursor
- NLP chips: purple bg + white text for category, gold wash bg for date/time
- "Add" button: rich gold (#B8860B) bg + white text (4.8:1 contrast)
- Voice waveform: deep purple base, rich gold peaks (not electric gold)

D2. TASK DETAIL (Light):
- Hero header: gradient from white -> subtle gold wash (#FFF8E1) if task has deadline today
- All inline edit fields: purple underline on focus
- Subtask segments: deep violet fill on light lavender track
- Activity timeline: purple dots + lavender connecting lines

D4. KANBAN (Light):
- Column headers: lavender bg (#EDE5F7) + purple text
- Cards: white + purple shadow
- Dragging card: stronger purple shadow + scale 1.02
- Column glow on hover: lavender brightens to near-white

F1. CALENDAR (Light):
- Heatmap month cells (light mode scale):
  0 tasks: #F8F5FF (same as bg — invisible)
  1-2: #EDE5F7 (light violet)
  3-5: #D0BCFF (medium violet)
  6-9: #6B21A8 (brand violet — BOLD)
  10+: #B8860B (rich gold — legendary)
- Current time line: rich gold (#B8860B) — visible on white bg
- Task blocks: project color at 15% opacity fill + 2px left border at full project color

F3. POMODORO (Light):
- Timer ring: rich gold (#B8860B) fill on lavender track
- Background: #F8F5FF with very subtle warm tint
- Ambient particles: reduced opacity (20% vs 30% in dark). Darker tint particles.
  Rain = deep blue-gray. Forest = deep green. Cafe = deep brown-orange.
- Break mode: warm #FFF8E1 wash, emerald ring

G. GHOST MODE (Light -> Dark Override):
- Ghost Mode ALWAYS uses dark aesthetics regardless of system theme
- Entering from light: UI fades out -> bg crossfades #F8F5FF -> deep purple (400ms)
- This transition IS the design moment. The world shifts. Focus begins.
- Exiting: reverse crossfade. Purple melts back to lavender mist.
- The contrast between light app and dark Ghost Mode makes it feel MORE impactful

H1. CONTENT FEED (Light):
- Full-screen quote: backgrounds use DEEPER versions of category gradients
  Stoic: #1A0533 -> #2D1B69 (STILL dark — quotes look best on dark bg even in light mode)
  Option: user toggle "Light quotes" uses #F8F5FF bg + #1A0533 text + #B8860B accents
- Content cards in feed: white + purple shadow + Playfair in midnight purple
- Share cards: ALWAYS generated in dark mode aesthetic (social media impact)

H3. MORNING RITUAL (Light):
- Sunrise progression adapts: starts from lavender (#F0EAFC), not from night
  Step 1: #F0EAFC (cool lavender)
  Step 2: #F8F5FF (warming)
  Step 3: #FFF8E1 (gold dawn wash)
  Step 4: warm peach tint
  Step 5: full warm gold wash
  Step 6: gold shimmer on lavender
- Mood slider: purple (drained) -> rich gold (energized) on light gradient track
- Gratitude glow: each word highlights with gold wash bg (not gold text glow)

H4. EVENING REVIEW (Light):
- Moonrise: starts warm (#FFF8E1), dims to cool (#F0EAFC -> #EDE5F7)
- Final state: deep lavender, not midnight. Light mode stays light even at "night"
- Ring replay: same animation, rings use standard light mode colors

I1. PROGRESS HUB (Light):
- Heatmap: see F1 calendar color scale above
- Streak counter: flame Rive uses richer warm tones. Number in #1A0533.
- Personal bests cards: white glass cards + purple shadow + #1A0533 stat values
- Weekly sparklines: deep violet line on lavender track

I2. DASHBOARD (Light):
- Charts: deep violet lines on #F8F5FF bg. Area fill = light lavender gradient
- Gold highlights only for "today" or "best" markers
- Polar chart: purple segments, gold peak segments
- Sankey: purple flows, gold for completed path

I4. GAME MODE (Light):
- XP bar: rich gold fill (#B8860B) on lavender track
- Badges: white glass cards + purple shadow. Gold border for earned. Purple silhouette for locked.
- Level text: #1A0533 + small gold accent

J1. CHANNEL HUB (Light):
- Channel cards: white + purple shadow
- Connected = deep emerald chip (#059669) bg + white text
- "Test" button: deep violet outline
- Pro badge: deep violet bg + white text
- Usage bars: deep violet fill on lavender track. Quota warning = deep amber.

L1. PROFILE (Light):
- Avatar ring: Free = deep violet. Pro = rich gold (#B8860B) shimmer. Team = violet+gold.
- Stat numbers: #1A0533 in Bebas Neue
- Heatmap: light mode color scale (lavender -> violet -> gold)
- Plan badge: Pro = gold wash bg + rich gold border. Free = purple outline.

M1. SETTINGS (Light):
- Glass card groups: white + purple-tinted shadow + purple left border accents
- Toggle switches: deep violet active state, lavender inactive
- Theme preview: mini phone mockup shows ACTUAL light/dark preview side by side
- Sound library icons: deep purple icons on white. Active = gold wash bg.

M2. PLAN & BILLING (Light):
- Free card: white + purple border
- Pro card: gold wash bg (#FFF8E1) + rich gold border + subtle gold shimmer
- CTA button: rich gold bg + white text. "Start 7-Day Free Trial"
- Social proof counter: deep violet text


## 6.5 LIGHT MODE ANIMATION ADAPTATIONS

All animations work in both modes with these adjustments:

TASK COMPLETION:
- Dark: checkbox fills with #FFD700 (electric gold), gold ripple glow
- Light: checkbox fills with #B8860B (rich gold), gold WASH expansion (no glow — glow invisible on light)

PROGRESS RINGS:
- Dark: glow effect on 100% (outer glow visible on dark bg)
- Light: NO glow (invisible). Instead: ring THICKENS briefly + #B8860B shimmer

STREAK FLAME:
- Colors identical (fire looks natural in both modes)
- But: flame has subtle purple shadow on light mode (grounds it visually)

SWIPE ACTIONS:
- Dark: green/red REVEAL behind card
- Light: green/red REVEAL but slightly darker shades (#059669/#E11D48) for contrast

GHOST MODE ENTER:
- Dark: UI fades out, deep purple gradient fades in
- Light: UI fades out, #F8F5FF crossfades to deep purple (DRAMATIC shift)

PULL TO REFRESH:
- Dark: UNJYNX logo with gold shimmer
- Light: UNJYNX logo in deep purple + gold accent, no shimmer (cleaner)

SKELETON LOADING:
- Dark: purple shimmer on dark surface (#1D1B20 -> #2B2930 shimmer)
- Light: lavender shimmer on white (#F8F5FF -> #EDE5F7 shimmer)

PARTICLES (all types):
- Light mode: 30% particle count of dark mode
- 20-30% less opacity per particle
- Deeper tint (dark purple instead of light purple)
- Movement amplitude: 50% of dark mode (light = calm, not immersive)


## 6.6 LIGHT MODE EMPTY STATES

- Illustrations use deeper purple/gold on #F8F5FF (bold, grounded feel vs luminous in dark)
- Gold accents: #B8860B in light (not #FFD700 which washes out)
- Lottie animations: same but with alternate color set
- Background particles/sparkles: 30% less opacity in light mode
- CTA buttons: rich gold bg + white text (not electric gold)


## 6.7 LIGHT MODE SEASONAL VARIATIONS

- Snowfall: slightly darker snowflakes for visibility
- Diwali: warm orange tint works naturally on both modes
- Halloween: purple fog = rgba(107,33,168,0.06) overlay (subtle, not muddy)
- Late night auto-dim: shifts to warmer lower-contrast variant (NOT auto-switch to dark)
- Gold accents in ALL seasonal: #B8860B consistently
- Confetti: deeper tints for visibility on light bg


## 6.8 LIGHT MODE WIDGET THEMING

Widgets respect SYSTEM theme (not app theme):
- Dark widget: midnight purple bg (#0F0A1A), snow white text, gold accents
- Light widget: purple mist bg (#F8F5FF), midnight purple text, rich gold accents (#B8860B)
- Widget border radius: 16dp (matches OS widget style)
- Light widget cards: white + subtle purple border
- Light widget progress rings: same colors (vibrant enough on light)


## 6.9 THE LIGHT MODE DIFFERENTIATOR

What makes UNJYNX light mode BETTER than competitors:

TODOIST light: Pure white bg, gray text, red accent. Generic.
UNJYNX light: Purple mist bg, midnight purple text, rich gold accent. Warm, branded.

TICKTICK light: Blue accent on white. Every productivity app does this.
UNJYNX light: Purple + gold on warm off-white. Nobody does this.

THINGS 3 light: Excellent but ONLY blue accent. No personality.
UNJYNX light: Deep violet + rich gold + warm purple bg = strong brand identity.

NOTION light: Neutral, almost colorless. Intentionally bland.
UNJYNX light: Intentionally warm, purple-tinted, gold-accented. Opinionated.

THE KEY INSIGHT: Most apps design dark mode first and make light mode an afterthought
(just invert colors). UNJYNX designs BOTH as first-class. The purple mist background,
the purple-tinted shadows, the deepened semantic colors, the gold wash selections —
these are NOT automatic inversions. They are deliberate choices that make light mode
feel like a DIFFERENT premium experience of the SAME brand.

A user who uses light mode should feel like UNJYNX was DESIGNED for light mode.
A user who uses dark mode should feel like UNJYNX was DESIGNED for dark mode.
Neither should feel like the afterthought. That's the standard.
